\par Mage Armor
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Conjuration (Creation) [Force]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 1
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, F
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Creature touched
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 hour/level (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates (harmless)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par An invisible but tangible field of force surrounds the subject of a }{\i\fs20\cf0 mage armor }{\fs20\cf0 spell, providing a +4 armor bonus to AC.
\par Unlike mundane armor, }{\i\fs20\cf0 mage armor }{\fs20\cf0 entails no armor check penalty, arcane spell failure chance, or speed reduction. Since }{\i\fs20\cf0 mage armor }{\fs20\cf0 is made of force, incorporeal creatures can\rquote 
t bypass it the way they do normal armor.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Focus: }{\fs20\cf0 A piece of cured leather.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Mage Hand
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Transmutation
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 0, Sor/Wiz 0
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  One nonmagical, unattended object weighing up to 5 lb.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Concentration
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par You point your finger at an object and can lift it and move it at will from a distance. As a move action, you can propel the object as far as 15 feet in any direction, though the spell ends if the distance between you and the object ever exceeds the spell
\rquote s range.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Mage\rquote s Disjunction
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Abjuration
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level: }{\fs20\cf0 Magic 9, Sor/Wiz 9
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  All magical effects and magic items within a 40-ft.-radius burst
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates (object)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par All magical effects and magic items within the radius of the spell, except for those that you carry or touch, are disjoined. That is, spells and spell-like effects are separated into their individual components (ending the effect as a }{\i\fs20\cf0 
dispel magic }{\fs20\cf0 spell does), and each permanent magic item must make a successful Will save or be turned into a normal item. An item in a creature\rquote s possession uses its own Will save bonus or its possessor\rquote 
s Will save bonus, whichever is higher.
\par You also have a 1% chance per caster level of destroying an }{\i\fs20\cf0 antimagic field. }{\fs20\cf0 If the }{\i\fs20\cf0 antimagic field }{\fs20\cf0 survives the }{\i\fs20\cf0 disjunction, }{\fs20\cf0 no items within it are disjoined.
\par Even artifacts are subject to }{\i\fs20\cf0 disjunction, }{\fs20\cf0 though there is only a 1% chance per caster level of actually affecting such powerful i
tems. Additionally, if an artifact is destroyed, you must make a DC 25 Will save or permanently lose all spellcasting abilities. (These abilities cannot be recovered by mortal magic, not even }{\i\fs20\cf0 miracle }{\fs20\cf0 or }{\i\fs20\cf0 wish}{
\fs20\cf0 .)
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Note: }{\fs20\cf0 Destroying artifacts is a dangerous business, and it is 95% likely to attract the attention of some powerful being who has an interest in or connection with the device.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Mage\rquote s Faithful Hound
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Conjuration (Creation)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 5
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Effect:}{\fs20\cf0  Phantom watchdog
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 hour/caster level or until discharged, then 1 round/caster level; see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par You conjure up a phantom watchdog that is invisible to everyone but yourself.
 It then guards the area where it was conjured (it does not move). The hound immediately starts barking loudly if any Small or larger creature approaches within 30 feet of it. (Those within 30 feet of the hound when it is conjured may move about in the ar
ea, but if they leave and return, they activate the barking.) The hound sees invisible and ethereal creatures. It does not react to figments, but it does react to shadow illusions.
\par If an intruder approaches to within 5 feet of the hound, the dog stops barking and delivers a vicious bite (+10 attack bonus, 2d6+3 points of piercing damage) once per round. The dog also gets the bonuses appropriate to an invisible creature.
\par The dog is considered ready to bite intruders, so it delivers its first bite on the intruder\rquote s turn. Its bite is the equivalent of a magic weapon for the purpose of damage reduction. The hound cannot be attacked, but it can be dispelled.
\par The spell lasts for 1 hour per caster level, but once the hound begins barking, it lasts only 1 round per caster level. If you are ever more than 100 feet distant from the hound, the spell ends.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A tiny silver whistle, a piece of bone, and a thread.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Mage\rquote s Lucubration
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Transmutation
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level: }{\fs20\cf0 Wiz 6
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Personal
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  You
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par You instantly recall any one spell of 5th level or lower that you have used during the past 24 hours. The spell must have been actually cast during that period. The recalled spell is stored in your mind as through prepared in the normal fashion.
\par If the recalled spell requires material components, you must provide them. The recovered spell is not usable until the material components are available.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Mage\rquote s Magnificent Mansion
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Conjuration (Creation)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 7
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, F
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Effect:}{\fs20\cf0  Extradimensional mansion, up to three 10-ft. cubes/level (S)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  2 hours/level (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par Y
ou conjure up an extradimensional dwelling that has a single entrance on the plane from which the spell was cast. The entry point looks like a faint shimmering in the air that is 4 feet wide and 8 feet high. Only those you designate may enter the mansion,
 
and the portal is shut and made invisible behind you when you enter. You may open it again from your own side at will. Once observers have passed beyond the entrance, they are in a magnificent foyer with numerous chambers beyond. The atmosphere is clean, 
fresh, and warm.
\par You can create any floor plan you desire to the limit of the spell\rquote s effect. The place is furnished and contains sufficient foodstuffs to serve a nine-course banquet to a dozen people per caster level. A staff of near-transparent servants (
as many as two per caster level), liveried and obedient, wait upon all who enter. The servants function as }{\i\fs20\cf0 unseen servant }{\fs20\cf0 spells except that they are visible and can go anywhere in the mansion.
\par Since the place can be entered only through its special portal, outside conditions do not affect the mansion, nor do conditions inside it pass to the plane beyond.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Focus: }{\fs20\cf0 A miniature portal carved from ivory, a small piece of polished marble, and a tiny silver spoon (each item worth 5 gp).
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Mage\rquote s Private Sanctum
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Abjuration
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 5
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  10 minutes
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  30-ft. cube/level (S)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  24 hours (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par This spell ensures privacy. Anyone looking into the area from outside sees only a dark, foggy mass. Darkvision cannot penetrate it. No sounds, no matter how loud, can escape the area, so nobody can eavesdrop from outside. Those inside can see out normally
.
\par Divination (scrying) spells cannot perceive anything within the area, and those within are immune to }{\i\fs20\cf0 detect thoughts}{\fs20\cf0 
. The ward prevents speech between those inside and those outside (because it blocks sound), but it does not prevent other communication, such as a }{\i\fs20\cf0 sending }{\fs20\cf0 or }{\i\fs20\cf0 message }{\fs20\cf0 
spell, or telepathic communication, such as that between a wizard and her familiar.
\par The spell does not prevent creatures or objects from moving into and out of the area.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Mage\rquote s private sanctum }{\fs20\cf0 can be made permanent with a }{\i\fs20\cf0 permanency }{\fs20\cf0 spell.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A thin sheet of lead, a piece of opaque glass, a wad of cotton or cloth, and powdered chrysolite.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Mage\rquote s Sword
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Force]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 7
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, F
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Effect:}{\fs20\cf0  One sword
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 round/level (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par This spell brings into being a shimmering, swordlike plane of force. The sword strikes at any opponent within its range, as you desire, starting in the rou
nd that you cast the spell. The sword attacks its designated target once each round on your turn. Its attack bonus is equal to your caster level + your Int bonus or your Cha bonus (for wizards or sorcerers, respectively) with an additional +3 enhancement 
bonus. As a force effect, it can strike ethereal and incorporeal creatures. It deals 4d6+3 points of force damage, with a threat range of 19\endash 20 and a critical multiplier of x2.
\par The sword always strikes from your direction. It does not get a bonus for flanki
ng or help a combatant get one. If the sword goes beyond the spell range from you, if it goes out of your sight, or if you are not directing it, the sword returns to you and hovers.
\par Each round after the first, you can use a standard action to switch the sword to a new target. If you do not, the sword continues to attack the previous round\rquote s target.
\par The sword cannot be attacked or harmed by physical attacks, but }{\i\fs20\cf0 dispel magic}{\fs20\cf0 , }{\i\fs20\cf0 disintegrate}{\fs20\cf0 , a }{\i\fs20\cf0 sphere of annihilation}{\fs20\cf0 , or a }{\i\fs20\cf0 rod of cancellation }{\fs20\cf0 
affects it. The sword\rquote s AC is 13 (10, +0 size bonus for Medium object, +3 deflection bonus).
\par If an attacked creature has spell resistance, the resistance is checked the first time }{\i\fs20\cf0 Mage\rquote s sword }{\fs20\cf0 strikes it. If the sword is successfully resisted, the spell is dispelled. If not
, the sword has its normal full effect on that creature for the duration of the spell.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Focus: }{\fs20\cf0 A miniature platinum sword with a grip and pommel of copper and zinc. It costs 250 gp to construct.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Magic Aura
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Illusion (Glamer)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 1, Magic 1, Sor/Wiz 1
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, F
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  One touched object weighing up
\par to 5 lb./level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  One day/level (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None; see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par You alter an item\rquote s aura so that it registers to }{\i\fs20\cf0 detect }{\fs20\cf0 spells (and spells with similar capabilities) as though it were nonmagical, or a magic item of a kind you specify, or the subject of a spell you specify. 
\par If the object bearing }{\i\fs20\cf0 magic aura }{\fs20\cf0 has }{\i\fs20\cf0 identify }{\fs20\cf0 cast on it or is similarly examined, the examiner recognizes that the aura is false and detects the object\rquote 
s actual qualities if he succeeds on a Will save. Otherwise, he believes the aura and no amount of testing reveals what the true magic is.
\par If the targeted item\rquote s own aura is exceptionally powerful (if it is an artifact, for instance), }{\i\fs20\cf0 magic aura }{\fs20\cf0 doesn\rquote t work.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Note: }{\fs20\cf0 A magic weapon, shield, or suit of armor must be a masterwork item, so a sword of average make, for example, looks suspicious if it has a magical aura.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Focus: }{\fs20\cf0 A small square of silk that must be passed over the object that receives the aura.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Magic Circle against Chaos
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Abjuration [Lawful]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 3, Law 3, Pal 3, Sor/Wiz 3
\par This spell functions like }{\i\fs20\cf0 magic circle against evil, }{\fs20\cf0 except that it is similar to }{\i\fs20\cf0 protection from chaos }{\fs20\cf0 instead of }{\i\fs20\cf0 protection from evil}{\fs20\cf0 
, and it can imprison a nonlawful called creature.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Magic Circle against Evil
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Abjuration [Good]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 3, Good 3, Pal 3, Sor/Wiz 3
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M/DF
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  10-ft.-radius emanation from touched creature
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  10 min./level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates (harmless)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No; see text
\par All creatures within the area gain the effects of a }{\i\fs20\cf0 protection from evil }{\fs20\cf0 spell, and no nongood summoned creatures can enter the area either. You must overcome a creature\rquote 
s spell resistance in order to keep it at bay (as in the third function of }{\i\fs20\cf0 protection from evil}{\fs20\cf0 ), but the deflection and resistance bonuses and the protection from mental control apply regardless of enemies\rquote 
 spell resistance.
\par This spell has an alternative version that you may choose when casting it. A }{\i\fs20\cf0 magic circle against evil }{\fs20\cf0 can be focused inward rather than outward. When focused inward, the spell binds a nong
ood called creature (such as those called by the }{\i\fs20\cf0 lesser planar binding, planar binding, }{\fs20\cf0 and }{\i\fs20\cf0 greater planar binding }{\fs20\cf0 
spells) for a maximum of 24 hours per caster level, provided that you cast the spell that calls the creature within 1 round of casting the }{\i\fs20\cf0 magic circle}{\fs20\cf0 . The creature cannot cross the circle\rquote 
s boundaries. If a creature too large to fit into the spell\rquote s area is the subject of the spell, the spell acts as a normal }{\i\fs20\cf0 protection from evil }{\fs20\cf0 spell for that creature only.
\par A }{\i\fs20\cf0 magic circle }{\fs20\cf0 leaves much to be 
desired as a trap. If the circle of powdered silver laid down in the process of spellcasting is broken, the effect immediately ends. The trapped creature can do nothing that disturbs the circle, directly or indirectly, but other creatures can. If the call
ed creature has spell resistance, it can test the trap once a day. If you fail to overcome its spell resistance, the creature breaks free, destroying the circle. A creature capable of any form of dimensional travel (}{\i\fs20\cf0 
astral projection, blink, dimension door, etherealness, gate, plane shift, shadow walk, teleport, }{\fs20\cf0 and similar abilities) can simply leave the circle through that means. You can prevent the creature\rquote 
s extradimensional escape by casting a }{\i\fs20\cf0 dimensional anchor }{\fs20\cf0 spell on it, but you must cast the spell before the creature acts. If you are successful, the }{\i\fs20\cf0 anchor }{\fs20\cf0 effect lasts as long as the }{\i\fs20\cf0 
magic circle }{\fs20\cf0 does. The creature cannot reach across the }{\i\fs20\cf0 magic circle, }{\fs20\cf0 but its ranged attacks (ranged weapons, spells, magical abilities, and the like) can. The creature
 can attack any target it can reach with its ranged attacks except for the circle itself.
\par You can add a special diagram (a two-dimensional bounded figure with no gaps along its circumference, augmented with various magical sigils) to make the }{\i\fs20\cf0 magic circle }{\fs20\cf0 
more secure. Drawing the diagram by hand takes 10 minutes and requires a DC 20 Spellcraft check. You do not know the result of this check. If the check fails, the diagram is ineffective. You can take 10 when drawing the diagram if you are under no particu
lar time pressure to complete the task. This task also takes 10 full minutes. If time is no factor at all, and you devote 3 hours and 20 minutes to the task, you can take 20.
